### English Title:
Helicopter Crash in Hudson River Turns Family Tour into Tragedy

### English Text Summary:
A tourist helicopter crashed into the Hudson River in New York, resulting in the deaths of six people, including children and their parents who worked for the German company Siemens. The family was visiting from Spain. The helicopter took off from Manhattan and followed a familiar route, flying around the Statue of Liberty before heading north along the river. After approximately 16 minutes, it crashed into the water. Witnesses reported that the helicopter flipped and began to spin before crashing. The National Transportation Safety Board stated that the helicopter lacked flight data recorders, and the cause of the crash remains unclear. Emergency services received reports of the crash shortly after it occurred.

